Brian's Sweet Pizza Sauce

Inspired By:  Iron_Mikes_Sweet_Sauce https://www.food.com/recipe/iron-mikes-sweet-tomato-pizza-sauce-the-spirit-of-cincinnati-113153

Wet Ingredients:
2  tablespoons olive oil
1  (28 ounce) can tomato puree

Fresh Ingredients:
3  cloves fresh minced garlic
1⁄2  tablespoon minced carrot

Dry Ingredients:
1  teaspoon dried onion, minced or chopped
1⁄2  teaspoon dried basil
1⁄2  teaspoon dried oregano
1⁄2  teaspoon dried thyme
1⁄4  teaspoon dried parsley
1⁄4  teaspoon salt
1 1⁄2  tablespoons honey
2  tablespoons brown sugar
fresh ground pepper, to taste

Process:

Heat oil over medium heat and bloom Garlic
Add remaining wet ingredients
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 30-60 minutes, uncovered.

Tips:

Baby Carrot, cut in half, microwave, use garlic press
Dark brown sugar yields a deeper red sauce
